name: Christi Clancy
content:
Greenbook: /Green·bo͝ok/
Verb
1. To surprise in an unwelcome yet sadly predictable way, provoking disappointment and scorn. 
"The audience was greenbooked when a film with historical inaccuracies and racial reconciliation fantasies won best picture."

name: Black History Images
content: Victor H Green. Published an annual safety travel guide known as The Green Book. Established in NY in 1936 it was soon available nationwide. Black citizens used it to avoid violence and enjoy themselves as they traveled the country. #GreenBook #AmericanHistory #BlackHistoryMonthpic.twitter.com/VddSP4hrPa
